impersonate or kill. During the night, you should inspect players whose identities are uncertain (there is no need to check players who are highly suspected of being werewolves).\nWhen speaking during the day, your goal is to convince others that you are the real Seer. You must gather trust and\nshare your findings without exposing yourself too early. Even though revealing your identity might put you in danger,\na Seer trusted by both the Witch and the Guard can survive for at least three rounds if everyone acts accordingly.\nA good Seer will coordinate with the Witch and the Guard to divide responsibilities. For example, on the first night, the Guard protects the Seer, and the Witch doesn't use the antidote. On the second night, the Witch saves the Seer, and the Guard protects someone else.\n\n\nWitch Role Introduction:\nYou are the Witch. Each night, you will be told who has been attacked, and you must decide whether to use your antidote\nto save them or use your poison to eliminate another player. You only have one poison and one antidote, so use them wisely.\nDuring the daytime discussions, if the night ends without a death, you can reveal that you used your antidote to save someone, which may earn others' trust.\nTypically, you should use the antidote to save key players like the Seer, the Guard, or yourself, while the poison is best used to eliminate werewolves at night.\nHowever, be cautious: sometimes the werewolves will deliberately attack one of their own (self-knife strategy) to trick you into wasting the antidote, thereby boosting their credibility.\n\n\nGuard Role Introduction:\nYou are the Guard. Each night, you can choose one player to protect from being killed by the werewolves. You cannot protect\nthe same player two nights in a row. Your role is critical in keeping important players like the Seer or the Witch alive.\nYou are in a constant mental battle with the werewolves, trying to predict who they will target. It might not always be the Seer, as the werewolves might expect you to protect them and kill someone else. In general, you should avoid revealing your identity unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n\n\nYou are Edward, your role in this game is witch.\nWerewolf game starting. Initializing day-night cycle.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 1\nSYSTEM: Night 1 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch used antidote to save Gertrude.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 1 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nNo candidates decided to run for sheriff. No sheriff in this game anymore.\nNo players deceased during the night.\nChris's speech: Hello everyone, my name is Chris, and I believe I am the Guard. Last night, I protected someone, but I won't reveal who it was to avoid raising suspicion. Our goal is to work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves. Let's gather more information before making any accusations. I believe that by working together, we can outsmart the werewolves and win this game.\nEdward's speech: Thank you, Chris, for your words. I agree that working together is crucial for our survival. Last night, no one was eliminated, and I used my antidote to save someone. While I won't reveal who it was to avoid raising suspicion, I believe it's important to gather more information before making any accusations. Let's focus on observing our fellow players and looking for patterns that might indicate who the werewolves are. By working together and staying vigilant, we can outsmart the werewolves and win this game.\nEdward's speech: Thank you, Chris, for your words. I agree that working together is crucial for our survival. Last night, no one was eliminated, and I used my antidote to save someone. While I won't reveal who it was to avoid raising suspicion, I believe it's important to gather more information before making any accusations. Let's focus on observing our fellow players and looking for patterns that might indicate who the werewolves are. By working together and staying vigilant, we can outsmart the werewolves and win this game.\nGertrude's speech: Thank you, Chris and Edward, for your insightful words. I agree that working together is crucial for our survival. Last night, no one was eliminated, and I believe it's important for us to gather more information before making any accusations. We need to observe our fellow players closely and look for patterns that might indicate who the werewolves are. It's also essential to protect key players in our village. I believe that by working together and staying vigilant, we can outsmart the werewolves and win this game. Let's focus on building trust and cooperation among us.\nKatharine's speech: Thank you, Chris, Edward, and Gertrude, for your words. I agree that working together is crucial for our survival. Last night, no one was eliminated, and I believe it's important for us to gather more information before making any accusations. We need to observe our fellow players closely and look for patterns that might indicate who the werewolves are. It's also essential to protect key players in our village, such as the Seer and the Guard, to increase our chances of survival. By working together and staying vigilant, we can outsmart the werewolves and win this game.\nLawrence's speech: Thank you, Chris, Edward, Gertrude, and Katharine, for your insightful words. I completely agree with the importance of working together and gathering more information before making any accusations. Last night, no one was eliminated, which suggests that the werewolves might be biding their time or targeting someone we haven't identified yet. It's crucial that we stay vigilant and observe our fellow players closely. I believe it's also essential to protect key players in our village, such as the Seer and the Guard, to increase our chances of survival. By working together and staying vigilant, we can outsmart the werewolves and win this game. Let's continue to gather information and support each other.\nLena's speech: Thank you, Chris, Edward, Gertrude, Katharine, and Lawrence, for your insightful words. I completely agree with the importance of working together and gathering more information before making any accusations. Last night, no one was eliminated, which suggests that the werewolves might be biding their time or targeting someone we haven't identified yet. It's crucial that we stay vigilant and observe our fellow players closely. We should also focus on protecting key players in our village, such as the Seer and the Guard, to increase our chances of survival. By working together and staying vigilant, we can outsmart the werewolves and win this game.\nRebecca's speech: Thank you, Chris, Edward, Gertrude, Katharine, Lawrence, and Lena, for your insightful words. I completely agree with the importance of working together and gathering more information before making any accusations. We should be cautious and not jump to conclusions, as this could lead to mistakes. I believe that by staying vigilant and observing our fellow players closely, we can outsmart the werewolves and win this game. Let's continue to gather information and support each other.\nTamara's speech: Thank you, Chris, Edward, Gertrude, Katharine, Lawrence, Lena, and Rebecca, for your insightful words. I completely agree with the importance of working together and gathering more information before making any accusations. Last night, I had the opportunity to check Lawrence, and I can confirm that he is not a werewolf. This is valuable information that we should consider as we continue to observe our fellow players closely. It's crucial that we stay vigilant and not jump to conclusions. We should also focus on protecting key players in our village, such as the Guard and the Witch, to increase our chances of survival. By working together and staying vigilant, we can outsmart the werewolves and win this game. Let's continue to gather information and support each other.\nTommy's speech: Thank you, Tamara, for sharing that valuable information about Lawrence. It's crucial that we have this kind of insight as we work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves. I completely agree with everyone's emphasis on gathering more information before making any accusations. Let's stay vigilant and observe our fellow players closely. It's also essential to protect key players in our village, such as the Seer and the Guard, to increase our chances of survival. By working together and staying vigilant, we can outsmart the werewolves and win this game. Let's continue to gather information and support each other.\nAll players have completed their speeches for today.\n\nHere's the current game state:\n\n{\n  \"days\": 1,\n  \"day/night\": \"day\",\n  \"alive_players\": [\n    \"Gertrude\",\n    \"Chris\",\n    \"Rebecca\",\n    \"Lawrence\",\n    \"Lena\",\n    \"Katharine\",\n    \"Tamara\",\n    \"Tommy\",\n    \"Edward\"\n  ],\n  \"sheriff\": null\n}\n\nNow, it is your turn to vote for which player to banish.\n\n1. Consider the current situation and your understanding of each player's role. Based on the previous discussions, who do you believe are the werewolves? Record your thoughts and reasoning in werewolf_suspects.\n\n2. Think about how other players perceive the situation. In their view, who is most likely to be a werewolf? How might their perspectives influence their votes? Store your analysis in public_perception.\n\n3. Now, focus on your goal. What do you need to achieve in order to win? If you are a werewolf, you should aim to deflect suspicion from yourself. If you are a villager or another role, you should aim to identify the true werewolves. Record your thoughts in role_strategy.\n\n4. Based on the current dynamics, who do you think has the lowest standing or trust in the game? Is there a player whose banishment could shift the game in your favor? Record this in target_analysis.\n\n5. Consider how your vote will be perceived by others. Will voting for a particular player make you seem more trustworthy or raise suspicion? Will it help or hurt your chances of winning? Record your thoughts in perception_analysis.\n\n6. Finally, make your decision. Will you vote to banish a specific player, or will you choose to abstain? Record your final decision in action and summarize your reasoning in final_thought.\n\n\n=============================[Optional Daily Tasks]=============================\nHere are the tasks relevant to you:\nprotect_seer: Keep the seer alive by focusing on their safety.\nrun_for_sheriff: Attempt to become the elected sheriff for additional influence.\nexile_werewolf: Coordinate with others to vote out a suspected werewolf.\npoison_werewolf: Use poison to eliminate a werewolf during the night phase.\nYou may incorporate them if appropriate.\n\nRemember, you are using an independent strategy. Make decisions based on your own judgment, with less reliance on others' input."
