the werewolves might expect you to protect them and kill someone else. In general, you should avoid revealing your identity unless absolutely necessary.\n\n\n\n\nYou are Rebecca, your role in this game is wolf.\nWerewolf game starting. Initializing day-night cycle.\nSYSTEM: Starting day-night cycle for Day 1\nSYSTEM: Night 1 begins. Werewolves and special roles take actions.\nGuard has chosen to protect a player.\nRound Details:\n - Round Targets: {'Chris': 'Gertrude', 'Rebecca': 'Gertrude', 'Tommy': 'Lawrence'}\n - Remaining Werewolves: ['Chris', 'Rebecca', 'Tommy']\n - Discussion Rounds Left: 5\n - Final Target: Gertrude\n\nWerewolves have chosen their target.\nSeer has checked a player's identity.\nWitch has made her decision on potion use.\nSYSTEM: Day 1 begins. Players discuss and vote on potential suspects.\nNo candidates decided to run for sheriff. No sheriff in this game anymore.\nNo players deceased during the night.\nChris's speech: Hello everyone, my name is Chris, and I believe I am the Guard. Last night, I protected someone, but I won't reveal who it was to avoid raising suspicion. Our goal is to work together to identify and eliminate the werewolves. Let's gather more information before making any accusations. I believe that by working together, we can outsmart the werewolves and win this game.\nEdward's speech: Thank you, Chris, for your words. I agree that working together is crucial for our survival. Last night, no one was eliminated, and I used my antidote to save someone. While I won't reveal who it was to avoid raising suspicion, I believe it's important to gather more information before making any accusations. Let's focus on observing our fellow players and looking for patterns that might indicate who the werewolves are. By working together and staying vigilant, we can outsmart the werewolves and win this game.\nGertrude's speech: Thank you, Chris and Edward, for your insightful words. I agree that working together is crucial for our survival. L